outline.guide:
The course aims to do the following: 
1.	To get extensive discussion experience through group chapter discussions and simulated negotiation activities (discussing prior to, during, and after each simulation);
2.	to develop an advanced theoretical knowledge of the field of negotiation and dispute resolution through the reading and analysis of the course textbook; 
3.	to gain wide-ranging experience of negotiation situations through the weekly negotiation simulations;
4.	to learn how to make effective and strategic plans for a diverse range of negotiations;
5.	to be able to recognize, deal with, and use bargaining tactics in negotiation situations;
6.	to learn about oneself through the weekly simulation experiences and subsequent post negotiation reviews and reflections;
7.	to develop targeted core competencies: creative competence to collect and utilize information, creative problem solving, communicative competence to deliver content and instructions effectively, and communicative competence of being able to clearly recognize and express one’s own thoughts and feelings, and to understand others' thoughts and feelings.
